					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You could use a scanline counting, but this would require good timing. As reference, set up a variable indexed with the timing (in cycles per frame). Every NMI would reset it to zero. As it's indexed properly, you linked it with the Y position of the objects - if any object's present, then analyse its X position in a certain range. You would do this 1 time per line, and killing it if the object is in range.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><strong>Zepper</strong><br /><a href="http://rocknes.web.fc2.com/" class="postlink"><em>RockNES developer</em></a></div>
